I believe that the 10th ammendment established 3 levels of government, Federal, State, and Personal.  Each of these levels of government enact legislation or rules... The Federal Laws, State Laws, and your own moral sense of right and wrong. <br>
<br>
The Judiciary system exists to determine at which level certain laws should lay.  It does this through legal review when someone brings grievance before it.  In a since, the Judiciary sits on the Bench and says, &quot;No you can't do that... that law should be held at the State level, or that law is something that people can decide on their own.&quot;<br>
<br>
